-- WAVE 4o REGRESSION FIXTURE — sample-driver per-claim marker count.
--
-- An exact copy of compiler/sample.ev (the lex-once `sample` driver), fed
-- a 1-enum + 1-claim source via stdin (see scripts/run-kernel-tests.sh
-- setup_fixture: the driver reads its source PATH from stdin line 1). The
-- source is the proven repro from tests/lang_tests/test_cons_chain_lit.ev:
-- the claim's `nums = ⟨…⟩` / `nums = ICons(…)` body stops the membership
-- walk, leaving leftover tokens. PRE-4o the driver re-dispatched those
-- leftovers as SIX `;; claim:` blocks (4 empty-name + a stray `ICons`);
-- the head_is_claimkw gate + skip_junk drain make it emit EXACTLY ONE
-- `;; claim: sat_user_intlist` (the enum emits NO marker — just its
-- datatype). The single broken `(assert (= nums ))` is a Wall-2 body-shape
-- gap (orthogonal; later waves), not a marker bug.
--
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-datatypes ((Result 0)) (((NoResult) (IntResult (IntResult__f0 Int)) (StringResult (StringResult__f0 String)) (RealResult (RealResult__f0 Real)) (EofResult) (ErrorResult (ErrorResult__f0 String)))))"
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-fun last_results () (Array Int Result))"
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-fun last_results__len () Int)"
-- expect: stdout = "(assert (>= last_results__len 0))"
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-datatypes ((IntList 0)) (((INil) (ICons (ICons__f0 Int) (ICons__f1 IntList)))))"
-- expect: stdout = ";; claim: sat_user_intlist"
-- expect: stdout = "(push)"
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-fun is_first_tick () Bool)"
-- expect: stdout = "(declare-fun nums () IntList)"
-- expect: stdout = "(assert (= nums ))"
-- expect: stdout = "(check-sat)"
-- expect: stdout = "(pop)"
--
-- compiler/compiler.ev — the self-hosted compiler driver.
--
-- This is the top-level program the whole project is building toward:
-- an Evident program that reads a `.ev` source file from disk, runs it
-- through lex → parse → translate, and emits the corresponding `.smt2`
-- to stdout. When compiled once via bootstrap to `compiler.smt2`, the
-- kernel runs THIS to compile every other `.ev` file, and bootstrap/
-- has no further role (see CLAUDE.md, "The architecture, in one
-- paragraph").
--
-- It composes the per-pass pieces that already exist:
--   compiler/lexer.ev            — char classifiers + Token enum
--   compiler/parser.ev           — Token/Expr/BodyItem AST + recognizers
--   compiler/parse_body.ev       — MembershipStep: one scalar membership / tick
--   compiler/parse_body_seq.ev   — SeqMembershipStep: one Seq membership / tick
--   compiler/parse_body_match.ev — MatchMembershipStep: one match membership / tick
--   compiler/translate.ev        — enum → (declare-datatypes …) (VariantText / EnumDeclSmtlib)
--   compiler/translate_declare.ev — BIMembership → (declare-fun …)
--   compiler/translate_arith.ev   — pin RHS Expr → SMT-LIB (atom / binop)
--   compiler/translate_match.ev   — match arm → nested ite
--   compiler/translate_seq.ev     — Seq surface → Z3 sequence theory
--
-- Nothing is hardcoded as tokens or AST: the source text is read from
-- disk and lexed character-by-character; the parse + translate flow
-- from the actually-lexed token payloads.
--
-- Pipeline shape — ONE multi-tick FSM, four phases keyed off `phase`:
--   * 0 LEX     — the consolidated-lexer accumulator FSM. One char per
--                 tick, prepending Tokens onto a (reverse-order) cons
--                 list carried in `_tokens`.
--   * 1 REVERSE — once lexing is done, pop the reverse list head and
--                 push it onto `fwd`, yielding forward (source) order.
--   * 2 PARSE   — TOP-LEVEL HEAD-TOKEN DISPATCH (grammar wave 3.5): the
--                 forward list's head token decides the program shape,
--                 mirroring bootstrap's program.rs (each top-level item is
--                 one of claim/type/schema/fsm/enum/import dispatched by
--                 head token).
--                   · `KwEnum`  → the enum-decl parse machine: walk the
--                     forward tokens ONE TOKEN PER TICK with an enum-parse
--                     state machine (ephase 1..8), building each variant
--                     and rendering it via translate.ev's VariantText.
--                   · otherwise → a claim head (`<kw> Ident`): drop the
--                     2-token head, walk the forward token list ONE
--                     MEMBERSHIP PER TICK, dispatching each membership by
--                     shape to MembershipStep (scalar), SeqMembershipStep
--                     (Seq), or MatchMembershipStep (match), accumulating
--                     the declare/assert lines (`out`) and the manifest
--                     state-fields (`fstr`).
--   * 3 EMIT    — the tick the parse walk drains: for a claim, assemble the
--                 manifest header + body and `puts` the .smt2; for an enum,
--                 assemble the (declare-datatypes …) block. Then Exit(0).
--
-- Grammar scope (docs/plans/grammar-wave1.md + wave2.md + wave3.md +
-- wave3.5.md): a claim head plus N memberships, each optionally pinned —
-- scalar/arith/comparison/boolean/ternary/string pins (waves 1–2), the
-- `= <atom> matches Ctor(_)` recognizer (wave 3), and — integrated into
-- this monolithic driver in wave 3.5 — a top-level `enum` declaration, a
-- `= match scrut { Ctor(b) ⇒ … ; _ ⇒ … }` membership pin (→ nested ite),
-- and `Seq(T)` memberships (⟨…⟩ literal / `++` concat / `#` cardinality).
-- is_first_tick is auto-injected and `_<name>` carry vars are excluded
-- from the manifest state-fields. Quantifier / subclaim / `..` / generics
-- and multi-top-level-item files are later waves.
--
-- Input path: stdin line 1 holds a per-process flat source path; tick 0
-- ReadLine's it, tick 1 ReadFile's it (wave 4o — no shared /tmp file, so
-- parallel sample-via-smt2 invocations don't race). See the INPUT block.

import "stdlib/kernel.ev"
import "compiler/lexer.ev"
import "compiler/parser.ev"
import "compiler/translate.ev"
import "compiler/translate_declare.ev"
import "compiler/translate_arith.ev"
import "compiler/translate_bool.ev"
import "compiler/translate_ternary.ev"
import "compiler/translate_match.ev"
import "compiler/translate_seq.ev"
import "compiler/parse_body.ev"
import "compiler/parse_body_seq.ev"
import "compiler/parse_body_match.ev"
import "compiler/translate_ctor.ev"
import "compiler/parse_body_ctor.ev"

claim main
    -- ── INPUT — per-process source path via stdin (wave 4o) ──────
    -- The shared /tmp/compiler-input.ev path (baked into a literal
    -- ReadFile) raced when sample-via-smt2.sh ran in parallel: every
    -- invocation's `cp $FLAT /tmp/compiler-input.ev` clobbered every
    -- other's mid-run. The fix is a tiny stdin protocol with no shared
    -- external state:
    --   tick 0 (is_first_tick) — emit ⟨ReadLine⟩; stdin's FIRST line is
    --     this invocation's per-process flat source path (a mktemp path,
    --     unique per wrapper invocation). It lands in last_results[0].
    --   tick 1 (¬is_first_tick ∧ ¬_got_path) — bind `src_path` from
    --     last_results[0] and emit ⟨ReadFile(src_path)⟩ (a DYNAMIC path,
    --     model-evaluated by the kernel). The file content lands in
    --     last_results[0].
    --   tick 2+ (_got_path) — `input` = the content; the lexer runs.
    -- `got_path` is a one-bit carry: false on tick 0, true from tick 1 on,
    -- so `¬_got_path` selects exactly tick 1 (the ReadFile tick).
    got_path  ∈ Bool
    _got_path ∈ Bool
    got_path = (is_first_tick ? false : true)

    src_path  ∈ String
    _src_path ∈ String
    path_read ∈ String = match last_results[0]
        StringResult(s) ⇒ s
        _ ⇒ ""
    src_path = (is_first_tick ? "" : ((¬_got_path) ? path_read : _src_path))

    input  ∈ String
    _input ∈ String
    content_read ∈ String = match last_results[0]
        StringResult(s) ⇒ s
        _ ⇒ "<no-read>"
    input = (is_first_tick ? "" : ((¬_got_path) ? "" : (_input = "" ? content_read : _input)))

    -- SAMPLE MODE: every top-level claim is sampled (name_selected = true
    -- below), so there is no target-claim selector — `target` is a dead
    -- constant kept only because name_matches/has_target reference it.
    target ∈ String = ""
    has_target ∈ Bool = (target ≠ "")

    -- ── LEX state (consolidated-lexer FSM, reverse-order tokens) ──
    -- `pos` advances by a state-computed `next_pos` (wave 4f bulk-skip)
    -- instead of a fixed +1: a whitespace run or a `--` line comment is
    -- consumed in ONE tick. `next_pos` is computed below, after the char
    -- classifications it depends on.
    pos  ∈ Int
    _pos ∈ Int
    next_pos  ∈ Int
    _next_pos ∈ Int
    pos = (is_first_tick ? 0 - 1 : ((¬_got_path) ? 0 - 1 : (_input = "" ? 0 : _next_pos)))

    partial_str  ∈ String
    _partial_str ∈ String
    partial_int  ∈ Int
    _partial_int ∈ Int

    cur_char ∈ String = substr(input, pos, 1)

    is_alpha ∈ Bool
    IsAlphaChar(c ↦ cur_char, out ↦ is_alpha)
    is_dig ∈ Bool
    IsDigitChar(c ↦ cur_char, out ↦ is_dig)
    is_ws ∈ Bool
    IsWhitespace(c ↦ cur_char, out ↦ is_ws)
    is_quote ∈ Bool
    IsQuote(c ↦ cur_char, out ↦ is_quote)
    op_tok ∈ Token
    is_op ∈ Bool
    SingleCharTok(c ↦ cur_char, t ↦ op_tok, recognized ↦ is_op)
    dig_val ∈ Int
    DigitToInt(c ↦ cur_char, n ↦ dig_val)

    done ∈ Bool = ((pos ≥ #input) ∧ (#input > 0))
    in_range ∈ Bool = ((pos ≥ 0) ∧ ¬done)

    was_collecting_str ∈ Bool = (#_partial_str > 0)
    was_collecting_int ∈ Bool = (_partial_int ≥ 0)

    -- ── String-literal mode (grammar wave 2; carried) ────────────
    -- A `"` opens the mode, chars accumulate, the closing `"` emits a
    -- StringLit token (escapes out of scope). While inside a string the
    -- normal ident/int collectors are suppressed (¬_in_strlit guards).
    in_strlit  ∈ Bool
    _in_strlit ∈ Bool
    partial_strlit  ∈ String
    _partial_strlit ∈ String

    strlit_open       ∈ Bool = ((¬_in_strlit) ∧ is_quote ∧ in_range ∧ (¬was_collecting_str) ∧ (¬was_collecting_int))
    strlit_continuing ∈ Bool = (_in_strlit ∧ (¬is_quote) ∧ in_range)
    strlit_closing    ∈ Bool = (_in_strlit ∧ is_quote ∧ in_range)

    in_strlit = (is_first_tick ? false
        : (strlit_open ? true
        : (strlit_closing ? false
        : _in_strlit)))
    partial_strlit = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (strlit_open ? ""
        : (strlit_continuing ? _partial_strlit ++ cur_char
        : (strlit_closing ? ""
        : _partial_strlit))))

    str_continuing ∈ Bool = (was_collecting_str ∧ is_alpha ∧ in_range ∧ ¬_in_strlit)
    str_finishing  ∈ Bool = (was_collecting_str ∧ ((¬is_alpha ∧ in_range) ∨ done))
    str_starting   ∈ Bool = ((¬was_collecting_str) ∧ is_alpha ∧ in_range ∧ ¬_in_strlit)

    int_continuing ∈ Bool = (was_collecting_int ∧ is_dig ∧ in_range ∧ ¬_in_strlit)
    int_finishing  ∈ Bool = (was_collecting_int ∧ ((¬is_dig ∧ in_range) ∨ done))
    int_starting   ∈ Bool = ((¬was_collecting_int) ∧ is_dig ∧ in_range ∧ ¬_in_strlit)

    partial_str = (is_first_tick ? "" : (str_continuing ? _partial_str ++ cur_char : (str_starting ? cur_char : "")))
    partial_int = (is_first_tick ? 0 - 1 : (int_continuing ? (_partial_int * 10) + dig_val : (int_starting ? dig_val : 0 - 1)))

    classified_str ∈ Token
    MaybeKeyword(s ↦ _partial_str, t ↦ classified_str)
    int_tok ∈ Token = IntLit(_partial_int)

    finish_str_only    ∈ Bool = (str_finishing ∧ (is_ws ∨ done))
    finish_int_only    ∈ Bool = (int_finishing ∧ (is_ws ∨ done))
    finish_str_with_op ∈ Bool = (str_finishing ∧ is_op ∧ in_range)
    finish_int_with_op ∈ Bool = (int_finishing ∧ is_op ∧ in_range)
    char_only          ∈ Bool = ((¬was_collecting_str) ∧ (¬was_collecting_int) ∧ is_op ∧ in_range ∧ ¬_in_strlit)

    tokens  ∈ TokenList
    _tokens ∈ TokenList
    strlit_tok ∈ Token = StringLit(_partial_strlit)
    tokens = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
            : (lx_comment ? _tokens
            : (strlit_closing ? TLCons(strlit_tok, _tokens)
            : (finish_str_with_op ? TLCons(op_tok, TLCons(classified_str, _tokens))
            : (finish_int_with_op ? TLCons(op_tok, TLCons(int_tok, _tokens))
            : (finish_str_only ? TLCons(classified_str, _tokens)
            : (finish_int_only ? TLCons(int_tok, _tokens)
            : (char_only ? TLCons(op_tok, _tokens)
            : _tokens))))))))

    has_input ∈ Bool = (#input > 0)
    lex_done ∈ Bool = (done ∧ ¬was_collecting_str ∧ ¬was_collecting_int ∧ ¬_in_strlit ∧ has_input)

    -- ── BULK-SKIP (wave 4f): whitespace runs + `--` line comments ──
    -- The wave-4e diagnostic (docs/plans/grammar-wave4e-perf-diagnostic.md,
    -- §5) found per-tick Z3 cost is flat ~490 ms and irreducible at the
    -- compiler.ev level, so total wall = per-tick × tick-count and tick
    -- count is the only lever. LEX was ~1 tick/char; a real .ev file is
    -- mostly whitespace + comments. We collapse those runs into one tick.
    --
    -- A whitespace run: WsRunLen returns the run length (capped 16); we
    -- jump past it. A lone separating space gives adv=1 (== old +1), so
    -- the token stream is byte-identical — only the tick count drops.
    --
    -- A `--` line comment (cur='-' ∧ next='-', at top level): jump to the
    -- next '\n' (via index_of) — or to end-of-input if none. This also
    -- closes the wave-4d Blocker-1 correctness gap (the lexer had no
    -- comment mode). Both skips fire only OUTSIDE a string literal and not
    -- mid-token, so they never swallow a real token boundary.
    lx_next_char ∈ String = substr(input, pos + 1, 1)
    lx_collecting ∈ Bool = (was_collecting_str ∨ was_collecting_int)
    lx_is_dash    ∈ Bool = (cur_char = "-")
    lx_next_dash  ∈ Bool = (lx_next_char = "-")
    lx_comment ∈ Bool = (lx_is_dash ∧ lx_next_dash ∧ in_range ∧ (¬lx_collecting) ∧ (¬_in_strlit))
    lx_nl ∈ Int = index_of(input, "\n", pos)
    lx_comment_to ∈ Int = (lx_nl < 0 ? #input : lx_nl)
    lx_skip_ws ∈ Bool = (is_ws ∧ in_range ∧ (¬_in_strlit))
    lx_ws_adv ∈ Int
    WsRunLen(s ↦ input, p ↦ pos, adv ↦ lx_ws_adv)
    next_pos = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (lx_comment ? lx_comment_to
        : (lx_skip_ws ? pos + lx_ws_adv
        : pos + 1)))

    -- ── PHASE control (0 lex · 1 reverse · 2 parse · 3 emit) ──────
    phase  ∈ Int
    _phase ∈ Int

    work_is_nil ∈ Bool = match _work
        TLNil ⇒ true
        _ ⇒ false
    work_hd ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ _work, out ↦ work_hd)
    work_tl ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ _work, out ↦ work_tl)

    entering_reverse ∈ Bool = ((¬is_first_tick) ∧ (_phase = 0) ∧ lex_done)
    in_reverse       ∈ Bool = (_phase = 1)
    entering_parse   ∈ Bool = ((¬is_first_tick) ∧ (_phase = 1) ∧ work_is_nil)
    in_parse         ∈ Bool = (_phase = 2)

    -- ── REVERSE: pop reverse-list head, push onto forward list ────
    work ∈ TokenList
    _work ∈ TokenList
    fwd  ∈ TokenList
    _fwd ∈ TokenList
    work = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (entering_reverse ? tokens
        : (in_reverse ∧ (¬work_is_nil) ? work_tl
        : _work)))
    fwd = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (entering_reverse ? TLNil
        : (in_reverse ∧ (¬work_is_nil) ? TLCons(work_hd, _fwd)
        : _fwd)))

    -- ══ TOP-LEVEL ITEM LOOP (grammar wave 4b) ═════════════════════
    -- Phase 2 walks a SEQUENCE of top-level items (wave 3.5 handled
    -- exactly one). A sub-mode `pmode` routes the forward stream
    -- `_items` (initialised to `_fwd` once REVERSE completes):
    --   0 DISPATCH — peek head(_items): KwEnum → enum (pmode 1); other
    --                non-empty head → claim (pmode 2); empty → all_done
    --                → EMIT.
    --   1 ENUM     — accumulate ONE enum's (declare-datatypes …) block
    --                into `eacc`, stopping at the next top-level keyword
    --                (or end of stream) rather than draining everything,
    --                then return to DISPATCH with `items` advanced to the
    --                remaining stream (the boundary keyword onward).
    --   2 CLAIM    — the wave-1..4 membership walk; on completion return
    --                to DISPATCH. In the real "N enum decls + 1 claim"
    --                translation-unit shape the claim is the last item;
    --                multi-claim selection (emit only the target claim,
    --                skip the imported Build* sugar claims) is a
    --                documented gap — see docs/plans/blocked-grammar-wave4b.md.
    -- The emitted unit is: manifest header · accumulated enum datatype
    -- blocks (`_eacc`) · the claim's is_first_tick decl + declares/asserts
    -- (`_out`), mirroring bootstrap's datatypes-before-declares ordering.
    pmode  ∈ Int
    _pmode ∈ Int
    items  ∈ TokenList
    _items ∈ TokenList
    eacc  ∈ String
    _eacc ∈ String

    items_hd ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ _items, out ↦ items_hd)
    items_nil ∈ Bool = match _items
        TLNil ⇒ true
        _ ⇒ false
    head_is_enum ∈ Bool = (items_hd matches KwEnum)
    -- A real top-level claim/type/schema/fsm head. Only THESE start an
    -- item; any other head token at dispatch is leftover from a claim
    -- body whose membership walk stopped early on an unsupported shape
    -- (Wall 2) — those tokens must be DRAINED (skip_junk below), never
    -- re-dispatched as spurious empty-name "claims" (wave 4o, Item 1+2).
    head_is_claimkw ∈ Bool = ((items_hd matches KwClaim) ∨ (items_hd matches KwType)
        ∨ (items_hd matches KwSchema) ∨ (items_hd matches KwFsm))

    -- A parametrized claim head is `<kw> Ident ( … )` — the token after the
    -- name is a LParen (wave 4g, Blocker 3). Such claims are the imported
    -- `Build*` sugar helpers; bootstrap's emit translates ONLY the target
    -- claim (the one passed to `emit`), inlining the helpers into it. We
    -- have no claim-name argument (the source is read from disk), so we use
    -- the corpus convention: the entry-point claim has NO first-line params,
    -- the helpers all do. So a parametrized claim is SKIPPED outright (its
    -- tokens consumed, no declares/asserts emitted); a bare-head claim is
    -- translated. `out`/`fstr` reset on each enter_claim, so when several
    -- bare-head claims appear the LAST one wins — the file's target claim.
    item_after_name ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ items_d2, out ↦ item_after_name)
    claim_is_param ∈ Bool = (item_after_name matches LParen)

    -- Claim-name selection (wave 4j): the token after the head keyword
    -- (head of items_d1) is this claim's name. When a target name was
    -- read (has_target), only the matching bare-head claim is translated;
    -- the rest join the skip path. With no target, name_matches is unused
    -- and dispatch reverts to "last bare-head wins" (backward compat).
    claim_name_tok ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ items_d1, out ↦ claim_name_tok)
    claim_name ∈ String = match claim_name_tok
        Ident(s) ⇒ s
        _ ⇒ ""
    name_matches ∈ Bool = (claim_name = target)
    -- SAMPLE MODE (wave 4m): every top-level claim is sampled, so there is
    -- no target selection — name_selected is unconditionally true. Each
    -- bare-head claim → enter_claim (translated body), each parametrized
    -- claim/type → enter_skip (empty body ⇒ trivially sat). Both append a
    -- (push)…(check-sat)…(pop) block to `sacc` below.
    name_selected ∈ Bool = true

    in_dispatch  ∈ Bool = (in_parse ∧ (_pmode = 0))
    enter_enum   ∈ Bool = (in_dispatch ∧ (¬items_nil) ∧ head_is_enum)
    enter_claim  ∈ Bool = (in_dispatch ∧ (¬items_nil) ∧ head_is_claimkw ∧ (¬claim_is_param) ∧ name_selected)
    enter_skip   ∈ Bool = (in_dispatch ∧ (¬items_nil) ∧ head_is_claimkw ∧ (claim_is_param ∨ (¬name_selected)))
    -- Leftover mid-claim token (not a top-level keyword): drop ONE and
    -- re-dispatch. Drains a partially-walked claim's tail without emitting.
    skip_junk    ∈ Bool = (in_dispatch ∧ (¬items_nil) ∧ (¬head_is_enum) ∧ (¬head_is_claimkw))
    all_done     ∈ Bool = (in_dispatch ∧ items_nil)
    in_enum_run  ∈ Bool = (in_parse ∧ (_pmode = 1))
    in_claim_run ∈ Bool = (in_parse ∧ (_pmode = 2))
    in_skip      ∈ Bool = (in_parse ∧ (_pmode = 3))

    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- CLAIM sub-machine (pmode 2): membership walk over `_items`
    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    -- Drop the 2-token `<kw> Ident` head off the current item.
    items_d1 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ _items, out ↦ items_d1)
    items_d2 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ items_d1, out ↦ items_d2)

    rem  ∈ TokenList
    _rem ∈ TokenList

    -- Per-membership shape discriminator: peek tokens t3 / t4 off `_rem`.
    --   `name ∈ Type = match …`   → t3=Eq, t4=KwMatch         → match
    --   `name ∈ Seq(T) = …`       → t3=LParen (compound type) → seq
    --   `name ∈ Int = #src`       → t3=Eq, t4=Hash            → seq (card)
    --   otherwise                 → scalar
    r_l1 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ _rem, out ↦ r_l1)
    r_l2 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ r_l1, out ↦ r_l2)
    r_l3 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ r_l2, out ↦ r_l3)
    r_t3 ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ r_l3, out ↦ r_t3)
    r_l4 ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ r_l3, out ↦ r_l4)
    r_t4 ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ r_l4, out ↦ r_t4)

    mem_is_match ∈ Bool = ((r_t3 matches Eq) ∧ (r_t4 matches KwMatch))
    mem_compound_seq ∈ Bool = (r_t3 matches LParen)
    mem_card_seq ∈ Bool = ((r_t3 matches Eq) ∧ (r_t4 matches Hash))
    mem_is_seq ∈ Bool = (mem_compound_seq ∨ mem_card_seq)

    -- Wave-4 constructor-application / nested-Seq RHS. CtorMembershipStep
    -- self-discriminates (ok=true only for a ctor-app or a Seq of ctor-apps),
    -- so `mem_is_ctor` is just its `ok` — it never hijacks a non-ctor line.
    -- Given highest priority below: a `name ∈ Seq(T) = ⟨Ctor(…)…⟩` line is
    -- ALSO `mem_is_seq` (compound type), but the ctor step must win.
    cts_decl ∈ String
    cts_assert ∈ String
    cts_field ∈ String
    cts_rest ∈ TokenList
    cts_ok ∈ Bool
    cts_eff_len ∈ Int
    CtorMembershipStep(rem ↦ _rem, decl ↦ cts_decl, assertln ↦ cts_assert,
        field ↦ cts_field, rest ↦ cts_rest, ok ↦ cts_ok, eff_len ↦ cts_eff_len,
        sigtab ↦ _sigtab)
    mem_is_ctor ∈ Bool = cts_ok

    -- Compose all three step-claims on `_rem`; select by shape. Distinct
    -- composition sites are α-renamed, so the unused ones are harmless.
    step_decl ∈ String
    step_assert ∈ String
    step_field ∈ String
    step_pinned ∈ Bool
    step_rest ∈ TokenList
    step_ok ∈ Bool
    step_saw_ift ∈ Bool
    MembershipStep(rem ↦ _rem, decl ↦ step_decl, assertln ↦ step_assert,
        field ↦ step_field, pinned ↦ step_pinned, rest ↦ step_rest, ok ↦ step_ok,
        saw_ift ↦ step_saw_ift)

    sqs_decl ∈ String
    sqs_assert ∈ String
    sqs_field ∈ String
    sqs_rest ∈ TokenList
    sqs_ok ∈ Bool
    SeqMembershipStep(rem ↦ _rem, decl ↦ sqs_decl, assertln ↦ sqs_assert,
        field ↦ sqs_field, rest ↦ sqs_rest, ok ↦ sqs_ok)

    mts_decl ∈ String
    mts_assert ∈ String
    mts_field ∈ String
    mts_rest ∈ TokenList
    mts_ok ∈ Bool
    MatchMembershipStep(rem ↦ _rem, decl ↦ mts_decl, assertln ↦ mts_assert,
        field ↦ mts_field, rest ↦ mts_rest, ok ↦ mts_ok)

    sel_decl ∈ String = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_decl : mem_is_match ? mts_decl : (mem_is_seq ? sqs_decl : step_decl))
    sel_assert ∈ String = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_assert : mem_is_match ? mts_assert : (mem_is_seq ? sqs_assert : step_assert))
    sel_field ∈ String = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_field : mem_is_match ? mts_field : (mem_is_seq ? sqs_field : step_field))
    sel_rest ∈ TokenList = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_rest : mem_is_match ? mts_rest : (mem_is_seq ? sqs_rest : step_rest))
    sel_ok ∈ Bool = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_ok : mem_is_match ? mts_ok : (mem_is_seq ? sqs_ok : step_ok))
    sel_pinned ∈ Bool = (mem_is_ctor ? true : mem_is_match ? true : (mem_is_seq ? true : step_pinned))
    sel_saw_ift ∈ Bool = ((¬mem_is_ctor) ∧ (¬mem_is_match) ∧ (¬mem_is_seq) ∧ step_saw_ift)
    -- max-effects derivation: only CtorMembershipStep reports a nonzero
    -- effects-literal length (the `effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨…⟩` state field).
    sel_eff ∈ Int = (mem_is_ctor ? cts_eff_len : 0)

    chunk ∈ String = (sel_pinned ? sel_decl ++ "\n" ++ sel_assert : sel_decl)

    claim_done ∈ Bool = (in_claim_run ∧ (¬sel_ok))

    rem = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (enter_claim ? items_d2
        : (in_claim_run ∧ sel_ok ? sel_rest
        : _rem)))

    out  ∈ String
    _out ∈ String
    out = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_claim ? ""
        : (in_claim_run ∧ sel_ok ? (_out = "" ? chunk : _out ++ "\n" ++ chunk)
        : _out)))

    fstr  ∈ String
    _fstr ∈ String
    fstr = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_claim ? ""
        : (in_claim_run ∧ sel_ok ? (sel_field = "" ? _fstr : (_fstr = "" ? sel_field : _fstr ++ " " ++ sel_field))
        : _fstr)))

    -- max-effects accumulator: the maximum effects-literal length seen across
    -- the whole program (bootstrap uses a fixed cap of 16 — see
    -- bootstrap/runtime/src/emit.rs:25,134; we derive a tight bound per the
    -- wave-4c task. Both are kernel-correct as long as the value ≥ the runtime
    -- effects length, which a single literal binding guarantees). Persists
    -- across items (program-global), so it is NOT reset on enter_claim.
    mxe  ∈ Int
    _mxe ∈ Int
    mxe = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (in_claim_run ∧ sel_ok ? (sel_eff > _mxe ? sel_eff : _mxe)
        : _mxe))

    -- is_first_tick auto-inject guard: track whether the source declared
    -- is_first_tick during the parse walk (mirrors bootstrap emit's
    -- ensure_is_first_tick_decl, which prepends the decl only when absent).
    ift  ∈ Bool
    _ift ∈ Bool
    ift = (is_first_tick ? false
        : (enter_claim ? false
        : (in_claim_run ∧ sel_ok ? (_ift ∨ sel_saw_ift)
        : _ift)))

    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- ENUM sub-machine (pmode 1): enum-decl parse machine
    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- ephase: 1 KwEnum · 2 name · 3 Eq · 4 variant-name · 5 after-name
    --         (LParen→6, Pipe/end→finalize) · 6 field-type · 7 after-field
    --         (Comma→6, RParen→8) · 8 after-fields (Pipe/end→finalize)
    plist  ∈ TokenList
    _plist ∈ TokenList
    ephase  ∈ Int
    _ephase ∈ Int
    ename   ∈ String
    _ename  ∈ String
    body    ∈ String
    _body   ∈ String
    first_v  ∈ Bool
    _first_v ∈ Bool
    cur_name  ∈ String
    _cur_name ∈ String
    fcount  ∈ Int
    _fcount ∈ Int
    fA  ∈ String
    _fA ∈ String
    fB  ∈ String
    _fB ∈ String
    fC  ∈ String
    _fC ∈ String
    -- Compound field-type accumulator (wave 4g, Blocker 2): a payload
    -- field type may be multi-token (`Seq(LibArg)`, `Map(Int, Int)`), so
    -- e6 now ACCUMULATES the type string with bracket-depth tracking
    -- (reusing parser.ev::TypeTokenText + BracketDelta) instead of reading
    -- a single Ident. `ftacc` holds the in-progress type text; `fdepth`
    -- the `(`/`<` nesting depth. A field is COMMITTED when a Comma (→ next
    -- field) or RParen (→ close ctor) is seen at depth 0.
    ftacc  ∈ String
    _ftacc ∈ String
    fdepth  ∈ Int
    _fdepth ∈ Int
    -- The Seq-payload element type seen in this enum (e.g. "LibArg" for
    -- `Seq(LibArg)`), used to emit the `__SeqOf_T` Cons helper datatype
    -- before the enum block. At most one distinct Seq element type per
    -- enum in the corpus (Effect's Seq(LibArg)); the last one wins.
    seqelt  ∈ String
    _seqelt ∈ String

    ptok ∈ Token = match _plist
        TLCons(t, _) ⇒ t
        TLNil ⇒ EofTok
    ptail ∈ TokenList = match _plist
        TLCons(_, t) ⇒ t
        TLNil ⇒ TLNil
    plist_nil ∈ Bool = match _plist
        TLNil ⇒ true
        _ ⇒ false

    p_is_enum   ∈ Bool = (ptok matches KwEnum)
    p_is_ident  ∈ Bool = (ptok matches Ident(_))
    p_is_eq     ∈ Bool = (ptok matches Eq)
    p_is_lp     ∈ Bool = (ptok matches LParen)
    p_is_rp     ∈ Bool = (ptok matches RParen)
    p_is_comma  ∈ Bool = (ptok matches Comma)
    p_is_pipe   ∈ Bool = (ptok matches Pipe)
    p_id ∈ String = match ptok
        Ident(s) ⇒ s
        _ ⇒ ""

    -- Per-tick field-type contribution + bracket-depth delta for the e6
    -- compound-type accumulator (wave 4g).
    p_bd ∈ Int
    BracketDelta(t ↦ ptok, d ↦ p_bd)
    p_tt ∈ String
    p_tt_is ∈ Bool
    TypeTokenText(t ↦ ptok, s ↦ p_tt, is_type_tok ↦ p_tt_is)

    e1 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 1)
    e2 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 2)
    e3 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 3)
    e4 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 4)
    e5 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 5)
    e6 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 6)
    e7 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 7)
    e8 ∈ Bool = (_ephase = 8)

    -- A top-level keyword at the enum head ends THIS enum (the next item
    -- starts there). This is the wave-4b multi-item stop: instead of
    -- draining the whole forward list, the enum machine halts at the next
    -- enum/claim/type/fsm/schema and leaves the remaining stream in `_plist`.
    p_is_tlkw ∈ Bool = ((ptok matches KwEnum) ∨ (ptok matches KwClaim)
        ∨ (ptok matches KwType) ∨ (ptok matches KwFsm) ∨ (ptok matches KwSchema))

    -- A variant is pending (name read, awaiting boundary) in e5 or e8.
    -- Variants are separated by `|` (Pipe) OR by a newline (the consolidated
    -- lexer emits NO Newline token, so a newline-separated next variant
    -- shows up as a bare Ident while pending — wave 4g). An Ident while
    -- pending therefore BOTH finalizes the current variant and starts the
    -- next one in the same tick.
    have_pending ∈ Bool = (e5 ∨ e8)
    at_boundary  ∈ Bool = (p_is_pipe ∨ plist_nil ∨ p_is_tlkw ∨ (have_pending ∧ p_is_ident))
    finalize     ∈ Bool = (in_enum_run ∧ have_pending ∧ at_boundary)
    -- This enum is complete: pending variant + we are at the end of the
    -- stream or the next top-level keyword (NOT a `|`, which continues it).
    enum_done    ∈ Bool = (in_enum_run ∧ have_pending ∧ (plist_nil ∨ p_is_tlkw))

    -- Reconstruct the EnumVariantDecl from the carried slots and render.
    cur_fields ∈ EVFieldList = (_fcount = 0 ? EVFNil
        : _fcount = 1 ? EVFCons(EVFType(_fA), EVFNil)
        : _fcount = 2 ? EVFCons(EVFType(_fA), EVFCons(EVFType(_fB), EVFNil))
        : EVFCons(EVFType(_fA), EVFCons(EVFType(_fB), EVFCons(EVFType(_fC), EVFNil))))
    cur_decl ∈ EnumVariantDecl = (_fcount = 0 ? EVDecl(_cur_name) : EVDeclP(_cur_name, cur_fields))
    rendered ∈ String
    VariantText(v ↦ cur_decl, out ↦ rendered)

    new_body ∈ String = (finalize ? (_first_v ? rendered : _body ++ " " ++ rendered) : _body)

    -- A payload field is COMMITTED when, in e6 at bracket-depth 0, we hit a
    -- Comma (next field) or RParen (close ctor). Otherwise the e6 token is
    -- accumulated into the compound type string (wave 4g).
    committing_field ∈ Bool = (in_enum_run ∧ e6 ∧ (_fdepth = 0) ∧ (p_is_comma ∨ p_is_rp))

    -- ephase transition. e6 is now a SELF-LOOPING accumulator: it stays in
    -- e6 while reading a (possibly compound) field type and on a Comma
    -- commit (next field), and exits to e8 only on a depth-0 RParen commit.
    -- e5/e8 + Ident is the newline-separated next-variant case (→ e5, the
    -- new variant's after-name state).
    next_ephase ∈ Int = (e1 ∧ p_is_enum ? 2
        : e2 ∧ p_is_ident ? 3
        : e3 ∧ p_is_eq ? 4
        : e4 ∧ p_is_ident ? 5
        : e5 ∧ p_is_lp ? 6
        : e5 ∧ p_is_pipe ? 4
        : e5 ∧ p_is_ident ? 5
        : e6 ∧ committing_field ∧ p_is_rp ? 8
        : e8 ∧ p_is_pipe ? 4
        : e8 ∧ p_is_ident ? 5
        : _ephase)

    -- A new variant starts on an Ident in e4 (after `=`/`|`) OR on an Ident
    -- while a variant is pending (e5/e8 — newline-separated).
    starting_variant ∈ Bool = ((e4 ∨ e5 ∨ e8) ∧ p_is_ident)

    -- State carry for the enum-parse sub-machine. `enter_enum` (re)inits
    -- it for each enum item; `in_enum_run` advances it; `enum_done` halts
    -- it at the boundary (without consuming the boundary keyword: plist is
    -- left pointing AT it so DISPATCH picks up the next item there).
    plist   = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (enter_enum ? _items
        : (in_enum_run ∧ (¬enum_done) ∧ (¬plist_nil) ? ptail
        : _plist)))
    ephase  = (is_first_tick ? 1
        : (enter_enum ? 1
        : (in_enum_run ? next_ephase
        : _ephase)))
    ename   = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_enum ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ e2 ∧ p_is_ident ? p_id
        : _ename)))
    body    = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_enum ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ? new_body
        : _body)))
    first_v = (is_first_tick ? true
        : (enter_enum ? true
        : (finalize ? false
        : _first_v)))
    cur_name = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_enum ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? p_id
        : _cur_name)))
    fcount  = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (enter_enum ? 0
        : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? 0
        : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ? _fcount + 1
        : _fcount))))
    fA = (is_first_tick ? "" : (enter_enum ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ∧ (_fcount = 0) ? _ftacc : _fA))))
    fB = (is_first_tick ? "" : (enter_enum ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ∧ (_fcount = 1) ? _ftacc : _fB))))
    fC = (is_first_tick ? "" : (enter_enum ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? "" : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ∧ (_fcount = 2) ? _ftacc : _fC))))

    -- Compound field-type accumulator carries (wave 4g). `ftacc` resets per
    -- variant (starting_variant) and on each field commit; in e6 it grows
    -- by the per-token type text unless this token commits the field.
    ftacc = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_enum ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ e6 ∧ committing_field ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ e6 ∧ (¬committing_field) ? _ftacc ++ p_tt
        : _ftacc)))))
    fdepth = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (enter_enum ? 0
        : (in_enum_run ∧ starting_variant ? 0
        : (in_enum_run ∧ e6 ∧ committing_field ? 0
        : (in_enum_run ∧ e6 ∧ (¬committing_field) ? _fdepth + p_bd
        : _fdepth)))))
    commit_is_seq ∈ Bool
    commit_elt ∈ String
    SeqEltType(set_ty ↦ _ftacc, set_is_seq ↦ commit_is_seq, set_elt ↦ commit_elt)
    seqelt = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enter_enum ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ∧ commit_is_seq ? commit_elt
        : _seqelt)))

    -- Variant-signature table (wave 4h, Item 1). For every payload field of
    -- type `Seq(T)` we record one `<ctor>#<idx>#<T>;` entry. The renderer
    -- (translate_ctor.ev::EltHintLookup) queries it by ctor name + arg index
    -- to lower a Seq VALUE in constructor-argument position to the
    -- `__Cell_T`/`__Empty_T` Cons form (Blocker 2c —
    -- docs/plans/blocked-grammar-wave4g.md). At commit time `_cur_name` is
    -- the variant name and `_fcount` the (0-based) index of the field being
    -- committed. Program-global: accumulates across all enums, NOT reset on
    -- enter_enum (the table must be complete before the claim phase renders).
    sigtab  ∈ String
    _sigtab ∈ String
    sigtab_entry ∈ String = _cur_name ++ "#" ++ str_from_int(_fcount) ++ "#" ++ commit_elt ++ ";"
    sigtab = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (in_enum_run ∧ committing_field ∧ commit_is_seq ? _sigtab ++ sigtab_entry
        : _sigtab))

    -- The (declare-datatypes …) block for the enum that just finished.
    grouped_body ∈ String = "(" ++ new_body ++ ")"
    cur_enum_decl ∈ EnumDeclAst = EnumD(_ename, EVNil)
    enum_block ∈ String
    EnumDeclSmtlib(decl ↦ cur_enum_decl, body_str ↦ grouped_body, out ↦ enum_block)

    -- Prepend the `__SeqOf_T` Cons helper datatype when this enum has a
    -- Seq(T) payload (wave 4g, Blocker 2) — it must precede the enum that
    -- references it, matching bootstrap's stage ordering. `Result` is
    -- skipped entirely: the kernel always pins it and the EMIT prelude
    -- already declares it (bootstrap dedups it the same way).
    helper_block ∈ String
    SeqHelperBlock(shb_elt ↦ _seqelt, shb_out ↦ helper_block)
    full_enum_block ∈ String = (_seqelt = "" ? enum_block : helper_block ++ "\n" ++ enum_block)
    is_result_enum ∈ Bool = (_ename = "Result")

    -- Accumulators (persist across items): enum datatype blocks, and the
    -- remaining top-level stream. `eacc` only grows on `enum_done`; `items`
    -- advances at the parse start, each enum boundary, and the claim end.
    eacc = (is_first_tick ? ""
        : (enum_done ? (is_result_enum ? _eacc
            : (_eacc = "" ? full_enum_block : _eacc ++ "\n" ++ full_enum_block))
        : _eacc))
    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- CLAIM-SKIP sub-machine (pmode 3): drop a parametrized helper claim
    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- Walk one token per tick from just past the skipped claim's keyword,
    -- halting at the next top-level keyword (or end of stream), then return
    -- to DISPATCH with `items` pointing AT that keyword. Emits nothing.
    skipl  ∈ TokenList
    _skipl ∈ TokenList
    skipl_hd ∈ Token
    TLHd(l ↦ _skipl, out ↦ skipl_hd)
    skipl_tl ∈ TokenList
    TLTl(l ↦ _skipl, out ↦ skipl_tl)
    skipl_nil ∈ Bool = match _skipl
        TLNil ⇒ true
        _ ⇒ false
    skip_at_tlkw ∈ Bool = ((skipl_hd matches KwEnum) ∨ (skipl_hd matches KwClaim)
        ∨ (skipl_hd matches KwType) ∨ (skipl_hd matches KwFsm) ∨ (skipl_hd matches KwSchema))
    skip_stop ∈ Bool = (in_skip ∧ (skipl_nil ∨ skip_at_tlkw))
    skipl = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (enter_skip ? items_d1
        : (in_skip ∧ (¬skip_stop) ? skipl_tl
        : _skipl)))

    items = (is_first_tick ? TLNil
        : (entering_parse ? _fwd
        : (enum_done ? _plist
        : (claim_done ? _rem
        : (skip_stop ? _skipl
        : (skip_junk ? items_d1
        : _items))))))
    pmode = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (entering_parse ? 0
        : (enter_enum ? 1
        : (enter_claim ? 2
        : (enter_skip ? 3
        : (enum_done ? 0
        : (claim_done ? 0
        : (skip_stop ? 0
        : _pmode))))))))

    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- SAMPLE EMIT (wave 4m): one (push)/(check-sat)/(pop) block per
    -- top-level claim, STREAMED to stdout as each claim finishes.
    -- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -- Lex-once amortisation: compiler.ev re-lexes the whole file for EACH
    -- claim (~90 s × N claims). This driver lexes ONCE and emits every
    -- claim's constraints in a SINGLE kernel run, wrapped so a standalone
    -- `z3 -in` decides each in turn. Shared decls (Result/last_results in
    -- the prelude, enum datatypes in `_eacc`) are puts'd BEFORE the first
    -- push, so (pop) never discards them; each claim's own member declares
    -- + asserts live INSIDE its push and are reset between claims (the z3
    -- push/pop gotcha — see docs wave-4m). The `;; claim: <name>` marker
    -- lets the wrapper map z3's sat/unsat line order back to claim names.
    --
    -- CRUCIAL: blocks are NOT accumulated into a carried state string — a
    -- growing multi-KB `_sacc` makes every subsequent tick assert
    -- `_sacc = "<KBs>"` and Z3's string theory then dominates (a single
    -- enums file measured at 44 min CPU). Instead each claim's block is
    -- emitted by a GUARDED `puts` on the very tick the claim finishes
    -- (claim_done / skip_stop), so nothing large is carried and the
    -- per-tick cost stays at compiler.ev's single-claim level. stdout is
    -- sequential across ticks, so the puts land in source order.
    --
    -- On claim_done the just-finished bare-head claim's body (ift_decl ++
    -- _out — exactly what compiler.ev's single-claim `smtlib` carries after
    -- the shared prelude/datatypes) is wrapped and emitted. On skip_stop a
    -- parametrized claim/type contributes an EMPTY body ⇒ trivially sat,
    -- matching bootstrap's verdict for every param claim/type in the corpus
    -- (a fidelity gap only for a param claim whose body is self-contradictory,
    -- which the lang corpus never exercises — documented in the wave doc).
    claim_block ∈ String = ";; claim: " ++ claim_name ++ "\n(push)\n" ++ ift_decl ++ _out ++ "\n(check-sat)\n(pop)\n"
    skip_block  ∈ String = ";; claim: " ++ claim_name ++ "\n(push)\n(check-sat)\n(pop)\n"

    -- The shared prelude+datatypes are emitted ONCE, on the first claim
    -- block (by which point all enums precede it in the corpus, so `_eacc`
    -- is complete). `did_prelude` is a cheap Bool carry — the only new
    -- state this driver adds over compiler.ev.
    emitting_block ∈ Bool = (claim_done ∨ skip_stop)
    did_prelude  ∈ Bool
    _did_prelude ∈ Bool
    did_prelude = (is_first_tick ? false : (emitting_block ? true : _did_prelude))
    need_prelude ∈ Bool = (emitting_block ∧ (¬_did_prelude))

    -- ── PHASE transition ──────────────────────────────────────────
    phase = (is_first_tick ? 0
        : (_phase = 0 ? (lex_done ? 1 : 0)
        : (_phase = 1 ? (work_is_nil ? 2 : 1)
        : (_phase = 2 ? (all_done ? 3 : 2)
        : 3))))

    -- ── EMIT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    -- The DISPATCH tick that finds the item stream empty assembles and
    -- `puts` the full translation unit, then Exit(0).
    emit_now ∈ Bool = all_done

    -- (compiler.ev's manifest header is intentionally omitted in sample
    -- mode — the output is consumed by `z3 -in`, which needs no manifest.)
    ift_decl ∈ String = (_ift ? "" : "(declare-fun is_first_tick () Bool)\n")
    datatypes ∈ String = (_eacc = "" ? "" : _eacc ++ "\n")

    -- ── EMIT PRELUDE (wave 4d) ─────────────────────────────────────
    -- The kernel ALWAYS pins `last_results__len` and decodes
    -- `last_results` as an `(Array Int Result)` (kernel/src/tick.rs).
    -- Bootstrap hand-writes this in emit.rs `result_and_last_results_decls`
    -- (the Result datatype + `last_results` array) plus the
    -- `last_results__len` decl + `(>= last_results__len 0)` assert that
    -- the injected `last_results ∈ Seq(Result)` membership produces. The
    -- self-hosted EMIT phase produces none of it, so we emit a fixed
    -- prelude mirroring bootstrap's exact output, between the manifest
    -- and the enum datatype / body declares.
    prelude ∈ String = ("(declare-datatypes ((Result 0)) (((NoResult) (IntResult (IntResult__f0 Int)) (StringResult (StringResult__f0 String)) (RealResult (RealResult__f0 Real)) (EofResult) (ErrorResult (ErrorResult__f0 String)))))\n"
        ++ "(declare-fun last_results () (Array Int Result))\n"
        ++ "(declare-fun last_results__len () Int)\n"
        ++ "(assert (>= last_results__len 0))\n")

    -- SAMPLE MODE EMIT: the shared decls (Result/last_results prelude +
    -- enum datatypes) are prepended to the FIRST claim block; each claim's
    -- push/check-sat/pop block is puts'd on the tick it finishes. No
    -- manifest header is needed — the output is fed to `z3 -in`, not the
    -- kernel (z3 ignores `;;` comment lines, so the `;; claim:` markers
    -- pass through harmlessly for the wrapper to read). At all_done we only
    -- Exit(0); the blocks were already streamed.
    block_now ∈ String = (claim_done ? claim_block : skip_block)
    emit_payload ∈ String = (need_prelude ? prelude ++ datatypes ++ block_now : block_now)

    -- tick 0: read the per-process source path from stdin line 1.
    -- tick 1 (¬_got_path): ReadFile that path (dynamic, no shared file).
    -- tick 2+: getpid filler / puts a block / Exit. (See INPUT above.)
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = (is_first_tick ? ⟨ReadLine⟩
        : ((¬_got_path) ? ⟨ReadFile(src_path)⟩
        : (emit_now ? ⟨Exit(0)⟩
        : (emitting_block ? ⟨LibCall("libc", "puts", ⟨ArgStr(emit_payload)⟩)⟩
        : ⟨LibCall("libc", "getpid", ⟨⟩)⟩))))
